    "code": "012", 
    "data": "بِسْمِ اللهِ الرَّحْمٰنِ الرَّحِيْمِ \nIn the name of Allah, the Beneficent, the Merciful.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ اِنِّیْ اَسْئَلُکَ بِاسْمِکَ الْعَظِیْمِ الْاَعْظَمِ \nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA BISMEKAL A’ZEEMIL A-A’ZAMIL \nO’ Allah! I beseech You through Your Name, the great, the most great,\nالْاَعَزِّ الْاَجَلِّ الْاَکْرَمِ \nA-A’ZZIL AJALLIL AKRAMIL\nthe most majestic, the most magnificent and the most noble.\nالَّذِیْ اِذَا دُعِیْتَ بِہٖ عَلٰی مَغَالِقِ اَبْوَابِ السَّمَآءِ لِلْفَتْحِ بِالرَّحْمَۃِ انْفَتَحَتْ \nLAZEE EZAA DO-EE’TA BEHI A’LAA MAGHAALEQE ABWAABIS SAMAAA-E LIL FATHE BIR-RAHMATIN FATAHAT \nIf You are requested therewith to open the closed doors of the sky these will open with Your mercy.\nوَ اِذَا دُعِیْتَ بِہٖ عَلٰی مَضَآئِقِ اَبْوَابِ الْاَرْضِ لِلْفَرَجِ انْفَرَجَتْ \nWA EZAA DO-EE’TA BEHI A’LAA MAZAAA-EQE ABWAABIL ARZE LILFARAJIN FARAJAT, \nIf You are requested thereby to remove the narrowness of the doors of the earth, they will be opened wide.\nوَ اِذَا دُعِیْتَ بِہٖ عَلَی الْعُسْرِ لِلْیُسْرِ تَیَسَّرَتْ \nWA EZAA DO-EE’TA BEHI A’LAL U’SRE LIL-YUSRE TAYASSARAT, \nIf You are requested thereby to make easy the difficulty, it will be made easy.\nوَ اِذَا دُعِیْتَ بِہٖ عَلَی الْاَمْوَاتِ لِلنُّشُوْرِ انْتَشَرَتْ \nWA EZAA DO-EE’TA BEHI A’LAL AMWAATE LIN-NOSHOORIN TASHARAT,\nIf You are requested thereby to restore the dead to life, they will rise from their graves.\nوَ اِذَا دُعِیْتَ بِہٖ عَلٰی کَشْفِ الْبَاْسَآءِ وَ الضَّرَّآءِ انْکَشَفَتْ\nWA EZAA DO-EE’TA BEHI A’LAA KASHFIL BAA-SAAA-E WAZ-ZARRAAA-E INKASHAFAT, \nIf You are requested thereby to remove misery and adversity, it will be removed.\nوَ بِجَلَالِ وَجْہِکَ الْکَرِیْمِ \nWA BE JALAALE WAJHEKAL KAREEME \nI beseech You through the Majesty of Your person,\nاَکْرَمِ الْوُجُوْہِ \nAKRAMIL WOJOOHE \nthe Most Generous\nوَ اَعَزِّ الْوُجُوْہِ\nWA A-A’ZZIL WOJOOHIL \nand the Most Honoured One,\nالَّذِیْ عَنَتْ لَہُ الْوُجُوْہُ \nLAZE A’NAT LAHUL WOJOOHO \nbefore Whom everybody bows down in submission\nوَ خَضَعَتْ لَہُ الرِّقَابُ \nWA KHAZA-A’T LAHUR REQAABO \nand all necks bend down in reverence\nوَ خَشَعَتْ لَہُ الْاَصْوَاتُ \nWA KHASHA-A’T LAUL ASWAATO \nand all voices become humbled\nوَ وَجِلَتْ لَہُ الْقُلُوْبُ مِنْ مَخَافَتِکَ \nWA WAJELAT LAHUL QOLOOBO MIN MAKHAAFATEKA, \nand all hearts tremble; through Your fear\nوَ بِقُوَّتِکَ الَّتِیْ بِہَا تُمْسِکُ السَّمَآءَ اَنْ تَقَعَ عَلَی الْاَرْضِ اِلَّا بِاِذْنِکَ \nWA BE QUWWATEKAL LATEE BEHAA TUMSEKUS SAMAAA-A AN TAQA-A’ A’LAL ARZE ILLAA BE-IZNEKA, \nand I beseech You through Your Might, which prevents the heaven from falling on the earth except with Your permission,\nوَ تُمْسِکُ السَّمٰوَاتِ وَ الْاَرْضَ اَنْ تَزُوْلَا\nWA TUMSEKUS SAMAAWAATE WAL ARZA AN TAZOOLAA, \nand which controls all the heavens and the earth so closely that they cannot move away from their positions;\nوَ بِمَشِیَّتِکَ الَّتِیْ دَانَ لَہَا الْعَالَمُوْنَ \nWA BEMASHIYYATEKAL LATEE DAANA (KAANA) LAHAL A’AALAMOONA, \nand I beseech You through Your Will, which the whole world obeys,\nوَ بِکَلِمَتِکَ الَّتِیْ خَلَقْتَ بِہَا السَّمٰوٰتِ وَ الْاَرْضَ \nWA BEKALEMAATEKAL LATEE KALAQTA BEHAS SAMAAWAATE WAL-ARZA, \nand through Your Word. By which You have created the heaven and the earth,\nوَ بِحِکْمَتِکَ الَّتِیْ صَنَعْتَ بِہَا الْعَجَآئِبَ \nWA BEHIKMATEKAL LATEE SANA’TA BEHAL A’JAAA-EBA \nand through Your Wisdom, with which You have created the wonders,\nوَ خَلَقْتَ بِہَا الظُّلْمَۃَ \nWA KHALAQTA BEHAZ ZULMATA \nand with which You created Darkness\nوَ جَعَلْتَہَا لَیْلًا \nWA JA-A’LTAHAA LAILAN \nand made it Night,\nوَّجَعَلْتَ اللَّیْلَ سَکَنًا \nWA JA-A’LTAL LAYLA SAKANAN \nand made night the time of quiet and rest;\nوَّ خَلَقْتَ بِہَا النُّوْرَ \nWA KHALAQTA BEHAN NOORA \nand with which You created Light\nوَ جَعَلْتَہٗ نَہَارًا \nWA JA-A’LTAHU NAHAARAN \nand made it Day,\nوَّ جَعَلْتَ النَّہَارَ نُشُوْرًا مُبْصِرًا \nWA JA-A’LTAN NAHAARA NOSHOORAN MUBSERAN, \nand made day the time of movement and observation;\nوَّ خَلَقْتَ بِہَا الشَّمْسَ \nWA KHALAQTA BEHASH SHAMSA \nand with which You have created the Sun,\nوَ جَعَلْتَ الشَّمْسَ ضِیَآءً \nWA JA-ALTASH SHAMSA ZEYAAA-AN, \nand made the sun gleam\nوَّ خَلَقْتَ بِہَا الْقَمَرَ \nWA KHALAQTA BEHAL QAMARA \nAnd with which You have created the Moon,\nوَ جَعَلْتَ الْقَمَرَ نُوْرًا \nWA JA-A’LTAL QAMARA NOORAN, \nand made the moon light;\nوَّ خَلَقْتَ بِہَا الْکَوَاکِبَ \nWA KHALAQTA BEHAL KAWAAKEBA \nand with which You have created heavenly bodies,\nوَ جَعَلْتَہَا نُجُوْمًا وَّ بُرُوْجًا \nWA JA-A’LTAHAA NOJOOMAN WA BOROOJAN \nand made them fixed stars and planets,\nوَّ مَصَابِیْحَ وَ زِیْنَۃً وَّ رُجُوْمًا \nWA MASAABEEHA WA ZEENATAN WA ROJOOMAN, \nand lamps for guidance at night, and as a means of decoration, and missiles for driving away devils,\nوَّ جَعَلْتَ لَہَا مَشَارِقَ وَ مَغَارِبَ \nWA JA-ALTA LAHAA MASHAAREQA WA MAGHAAREBA \nand have created for them east and west,\nوَ جَعَلْتَ لَہَا مَطَالِعَ وَ مَجَارِیَ \nWA JA-A’LTA LAHAA MATAALE-A’ WA MAJAAREYA, \nand have created for them the places of ascendancy and orbits,\nوَ جَعَلْتَ لَہَا فَلَکًا وَّ مَسَابِحَ \nWA JA-A’LTA LAHAA FALAKAN WA MASAABEHA \nand created for them a firmament and sphere,\nوَ قَدَّرْتَہَا فِی السَّمَآءِ مَنَازِلَ \nWA QADDARTAHAA FIS SAMAAA-E MANAAZELA \nand fixed for them stages in the heaven\nفَاَحْسَنْتَ تَقْدِیْرَہَا \nFA-AHSANTA TAQDEERAHAA, \nand how beautiful the stages\nوَ صَوَّرْتَہَا فَاَحْسَنْتَ تَصْوِیْرَہَا \nWA SAWWARTAHAA FA-AHSANTA TASWEERAHAA \nand shaped the stars and how beautiful the shapes\nوَ اَحْصَیْتَہَا بِاَسْمَآئِکَ اِحْصَآءً \nWA AH-SAYTAHAA BE-ASMAAA-EKA EHSAAA-AN \nand made them stable through Your Name;\nوَّ دَبَّرْتَہَا بِحِکْمَتِکَ تَدْبِیْرًا \nWA DABBARTAHAA BE HIKMATEKA TADBEERAN \nand from Your Wisdom You designed a system for them\nفَاَحْسَنْتَ تَدْبِیْرَہَا \nFA-AHSANTA TADBEERAHAA \nand what a good system,\nوَ سَخَّرْتَہَا بِسُلْطَانِ اللَّیْلِ \nWA SAKHKHARTAHAA BE-SULTAANIL LAYLE \nand controlled the heavenly bodies through the king of the night\nوَ سُلْطَانِ النَّہَارِ \nWA SULTAANIN NAHAARE \nand the king of day,\nوَ السَّاعَاتِ وَ عَدَدِ السِّنِیْنَ وَ الْحِسَابِ \nWAS-SAA-A’ATE WA A’DADAS SENEENA WAL-HESAABE, \nand through hours, making them a means for the reckoning of years and counting,\nوَ جَعَلْتَ رُؤْیَتَہَا لِجَمِیْعِ النَّاسِ مَرْئًی وَّاحِدًا \nWA JA-A’LTA ROA-YATAHAA LE JAMEE-I’N NAASE MAR-AN WAAHEDAN \nmaking appearance of heavenly bodies regular and universal.\nوَّ اَسْأَلُکَ اللّٰہُمَّ بِمَجْدِکَ الَّذِیْ کَلَّمْتَ بِہٖ عَبْدَکَ وَ رَسُوْلَکَ \nWA AS-ALOKAL LAAHUMMA BE MAJDEKAL LAZE KALLAMTA BEHI A’BDAKA WA RASOOLAKA \nAnd I beseech You, O Allah, through Your Glory, with which You addressed Your slave and Your Messenger,\nمُوْسَی ابْنَ عِمْرَانَ عَلَیْہِ السَّلَامُ \nMOOSABNA I’MRAANA A’LAYHIS SALAAMO \nMoosa son of Imran peace be on him,\nفِی الْمُقَدَّسِیْنَ \nFIL MOQADDASEENA \nwhile he was in the company of angels\nفَوْقَ اِحْسَاسِ الْکَرُوْبِیْنَ \nFAWQA EHSAASIL KARROOBEENA \nwhich address even the favourite cherubin could not ever hear,\nفَوْقَ غَمَآئِمِ النُّوْرِ \nFAWQA GHAMAAA-EMIN NOORE \nabove the clouds of light,\nفَوْقَ تَابُوْتِ الشَّہَادَۃِ \nFAWQA TAABOOTISH SHAHAADATE \nabove the box of evidence,\nفِیْ عَمُوْدِ النَّارِ \nFI A’MOODIN NAAARE \nwithin the pillar of fire\nوَ فِیْ طُوْرِ سَیْنَآءَ \nWA FEE TOORE SAYNAAA-A \non Mount Sinai,\nوَ فِیْ جَبَلِ حُوْرِیْثَ \nWA FEE JABALE HOOREESA \nand on Mount Hurees\nفِی الْوَادِ الْمُقَدَّسِ \nFIL WAADIL MOQADDASE \nin the Holy Valley\nفِی الْبُقْعَۃِ الْمُبَارَکَۃِ \nFIL BUQ-A’TIL MOBAARAKATE \nin the sacred tract of land\nمِنْ جَانِبِ الطُّوْرِ الْاَیْمَنِ مِنَ الشَّجَرَۃِ \nMIN JAANEBIT TOORIL AYMANE MENASH-SHAJARATE \nto the right of Toor Mountain-through a tree;\nوَ فِیْ اَرْضِ مِصْرِ \nWA FEE ARZE MISRA \nand again addressed him on the soil of Egypt,\nبِتِسْعِ اٰیَاتٍ بَیِّنَاتٍ \nBE-TIS-E’ AAYAATIN BAYYENAATIN, \nafter showing nine clear signs\nوَ یَوْمَ فَرَقْتَ لِبَنِیْ اِسْرَآئِیْلَ الْبَحْرَ \nWA YAWMA FARAQTA LE-BANI ISRAAA-EELAL BAHRA \nand on the day You split the sea for the Children of Israel,\nوَ فِیْ الْمُنْبَجِسَاتِ الَّتِیْ صَنَعْتَ بِہَا الْعَجَائِبَ \nWA FIL MUNBAJESAATIL LATEE SA-NA’TA BEHAL A’JAAA-EBA \nand caused springs to flow from a stone, thereby displaying wonders of Your might\nفِیْ بَحْرِ سُوْفٍ \nFEE BAHRE SOOF, \nin a deep sea;\nوَ عَقَدْتَ مَآءَ الْبَحْرِ فِیْ قَلْبِ الْغَمْرِ کَالْحِجَارَۃِ \nWA A’QADAT MAAA-AL BAHRE FEE QALBIL GHAMRE KAL-HAJAARATE, \nand on the day when You solidified the water of the sea in the midst of the storm,\nوَ جَاوَزْتَ بِبَنِیْ اِسْرَآئِیْلَ الْبَحْرَ \nWA JAA-WAZTA BE BANI ISRAAEELAL BAHRA \nand caused the Children of Israel to pass by it,\nوَ تَمَّتْ کَلِمَتُکَ الْحُسْنٰی عَلَیْہِمْ بِمَا صَبَرُوْا \nWA TAMMAT KALEMATOKAL HUSNAA A’LAYHIM BEMAA SABAROO \nand fulfilled Your excellent promises made to them because of their calmly endurance,\nوَ اَوْرَثْتَہُمْ مَشَارِقَ الْاَرْضِ وَ مَغَارِبَہَا \nWA AWRASTAHUM MASHAAREQAL ARZE WA MAGHAAREBAHAL \nand made them the inheritors of the East and the West in the earth,\nالَّتِیْ بَارَکْتَ فِیْہَا لِلْعَالَمِیْنَ \nLATEE BAARAKTA FEEHAA LIL-A’ALAMEENA, \nwherein there are blessings for all the worlds;\nوَ اَغْرَقْتَ فِرْعَوْنَ وَ جُنُوْدَہٗ وَ مَرَاکِبَہٗ فِی الْیَمِّ \nWA AGHRAQTA FIRAWNA WA JONOODAHU WA MARAAKEBAHU FIL YAMME, \nand You drowned Firawn and his armies and boats in the water.\nوَ بِاسْمِکَ الْعَظِیْمِ الْاَعْظَمِ \nWA BISMEKAL A’ZEEMIL A-A’ZAMIL \nAnd (I beseech You) through Your name, which is the most great,\nالْاَعَزِّ الْاَجَلِّ الْاَکْرَمِ \nA-A’ZZIL AJALLIL AKRAME \nthe most majestic, the most magnificent, the most noble;\nوَ بِمَجْدِکَ الَّذِیْ تَجَلَّیْتَ بِہٖ لِمُوْسٰی کَلِیْمِکَ عَلَیْہِ السَّلَامُ فِیْ طُوْرِ سَیْنَآءَ \nWA BEMAJDEKAL LAZE TAJALLAYTA BEHI LE MOOSA KALEEMAKE A’LAYHIS SALAAMO FEE TORE SAYNAA-A, \nand through Your glory, with which You revealed light to Moosa, Your addressee, peace be on him, on Mount Sinai;\nوَ لِاِبْرَاہِیْمَ عَلَیْہِ السَّلَامُ خَلِیْلِکَ مِنْ قَبْلُ فِیْ مَسْجِدِ الْخَیْفِ \nWA LE-IBRAAHEEMA A’LAYHIS SALAAMO KHALEELEKA MIN QABLO FEE MASJEDIL KHEEFE, \nand earlier radiated the light for Ibrahim, Your sincere friend peace be on him, in the mosque of al-Khayf;\nوَ لِاِسْحَاقَ صَفِیِّکَ عَلَیْہِ السَّلَامُ فِیْ بِئْرِ شِیَعٍ \nWALE ISHAAQA SAFIYYEKA A’LAYHIS SALAAMO FEE BEA-RE SHEE-I’N \nand for Ishaaq, Your chosen Prophet, peace be on him, in the well of sheya’,\nوَ لِیَعْقُوْبَ نَبِیِّکَ عَلَیْہِ السَّلَامُ فِیْ بَیْتِ اِیْلٍ \nWA LE YAA’QOOBA NABIYYEKA A’LAYHIS SALAAMO FEE BAYTE EELIN, \nand for Your Prophet Yaqoob, peace be on him, in Bayt Eel\nوَ اَوْفَیْتَ لِاِبْرَاہِیْمَ عَلَیْہِ السَّلَامُ بِمِیْثَاقِکَ \nWA AWFAYTA LE-IBRAAHEEMA A’LAYHIS SALAAMO BE MEESHAAQEKA \nand through Your Glory, with which You fulfilled Your promise to Ibrahim, peace be on him;\nوَ لِاِسْحَاقَ بِحَلَفِکَ \nWA LE-ISHAAQA BE HALFEKA \nand through Your Oath in favour of Ishaaq;\nوَ لِیَعْقُوْبَ بِشَہَادَتِکَ \nWA LE YAA’QOOBA BE SHAHADATEKA \nand through Your witnessing favouring Yaqoob;\nوَ لِلْمُؤُمِنِیْنَ بِوَعْدِکَ \nWA LIL-MOA-MENEENA BE WA’DEKA \nand through the fulfillments of Your promise to the faithful:\nوَ لِلدَّاعِیْنَ بِاَسْمَآئِکَ فَاَجَبْتَ \nWA LIDDAA-EE’NA BE ASMAAEKA FA-AJABTA, \nand through Your Names with which You accepted the prayers of supplications;\nوَ بِمَجْدِکَ الَّذِیْ ظَہَرَ لِمُوْسَی ابْنِ عِمْرَانَ عَلَیْہِ السَّلَامُ\nWA BE MAJDEKAL LAZEE ZAHARA LE MOOSABNE I’MRAANA A’LAYHIS SALAAMO \nand through Your Glory, which appeared to Moosa, son of Imran, peace be upon him\nعَلٰی قُبَّۃِ الرُّمَّانِ \nA’LAA QUBBATIR RUMMAANE \nin Qubbat al-Rumman;\nوَ بِاٰیٰتِکَ الَّتِیْ وَقَعَتْ عَلٰی اَرْضِ مِصْرَ \nWA BE-AAYAATEKAL LATEE WA QA-A’T A’LAA ARZE MISRA \nand through Your Signs, which appeared on the soil of Egypt\nبِمَجْدِ الْعِزَّۃِ وَ الْغَلَبَۃِ \nBE-MAJDIL I’ZZATE WAL-GHALABATE \nwith great might and victory,\nبِاٰیٰتٍ عَزِیْزَۃٍ وَّ بِسُلْطَانِ الْقُوَّۃِ \nBE-AAYAATE A’ZEEZATE WA BE SULTAANIL QUWWATE \nwith powerful signs and with the display of full command\nوَ بِعِزَّۃِ الْقُدْرَۃِ \nWA BE-I’ZZATIL QUDRATE \nand great power;\nوَ بِشَاْنِ الْکَلِمَۃِ التَّآمَّۃِ \nWA BE-SHAANIL KALEMATIT TAAMMATE, \nand with the affair of the perfect word;\nوَ بِکَلِمَاتِکَ الَّتِیْ تَفَضَّلْتَ بِہَا عَلٰی اَہْلِ السَّمٰوٰتِ وَالْاَرْضِ \nWA BE KALEMAATEKAL LATEE TAFAZZALTA BEHAA A’LAA AHLIS SAMAAWAATE WAL ARZE \nand with Your words with which You do a favour for the people of the heavens and the earth\nوَ اَہْلِ الدُّنْیَا وَ اَہْلِ الْاٰخِرَۃِ \nWA AHLID DUNYAA WA AHLIL AAKHERATE, \nand the people of this world and the hereafter;\nوَ بِرَحْمَتِکَ الَّتِیْ مَنَنْتَ بِہَا عَلٰی جَمِیْعِ خَلْقِکَ \nWA BE RAHMATEKAL LATEE MANANTA BEHAA A’LAA JAMEE-E’ KHALQEKA, \nand through Your Mercy with which You bestow upon all Your creatures:\nوَ بِاسْتِطَاعَتِکَ الَّتِیْ اَقَمْتَ بِہَا عَلَی الْعَالَمِیْنَ \nWA BIS-TETAA-A’TEKAL LATEE AQAMTA BEHAA A’LAL A’ALAMEENA, \nand through Your Power with which You dominate the worlds;\nوَ بِنُوْرِکَ الَّذِیْ قَدْ خَرَّ مِنْ فَزَعِہٖ طُوْرُ سَیْنَآءَ \nWA BE NOOREKAL LAZEE QAD KHARRA MIN FAZA-E’HI TOORO SAYNAAA-A, \nand (I beseech You) through Your Light, through fear of which Mount Sinai collapsed,\nوَ بِعِلْمِکَ وَ جَلَالِکَ وَ کِبْرِیَآئِکَ وَ عِزَّتِکَ وَ جَبَرُوْتِکَ \nWA BE-I’LMEKA WA JALAALEKA WA KIBREYAAA-EKA WA I’ZZATEKA WA JABAROOTEKAL \nthrough Your Knowledge, and Your Greatness and Majesty, and Your Unique Magnificence and Your Honour and (through) Your might,\nالَّتِیْ لَمْ تَسْتَقِلَّہَا الْاَرْضُ \nLATEE LAM TASTAQILLAHAL ARZO \nwhich the earth could not bear,\nوَ انْخَفَضَتْ لَہَا السَّمٰوٰتُ \nWAN-KHAFAZAT LAHAS SAMAAWAATO \nand, for which the heavens bent down,\nوَ انْزَجَرَ لَہَا الْعُمْقُ الْاَکْبَرُ \nWAN-ZAJARA LAHAL U’MQUL AKBARO, \nand the great depths restrained themselves,\nوَ رَکَدَتْ لَہَا الْبِحَارُ وَ اْلَانْہَارُ \nWA RAKADAT LAHAL BEHAARO WAL ANHAARO, \nand the seas and rivers became stable,\nوَ خَضَعَتْ لَہَا الْجِبَالُ \nWA KHAZA-A’T LAHAL JEBAALO \nand to which the mountains made submission,\nوَ سَکَنَتْ لَہَا الْاَرْضُ بِمَنَاکِبِہَا \nWA SAKANAT LAHAL ARZO BE MANAAKEBEHAA, \nand due to which the earth became firm on its shoulders,\nوَ اسْتَسْلَمَتْ لَہَا الْخَلَآئِقُ کُلُّہَا \nWAS-TASLAMAT LAHAL KHALAA-EQO KULLOHAA, \nand to which all creatures submitted,\nوَ خَفَقَتْ لَہَا الرِّیَاحُ فِیْ جَرَیَانِہَا \nWA KHAFAQAT LAHAR REYAAHO FI JARAYAANEHAA, \nand due to which the winds breathed,\nوَ خَمَدَتْ لَہَا النِّیْرَانُ فِیْ اَوْطَانِہَا \nWA KHAMADAT LAHAN NEERAANO FEE AWTAANEHAA, \nand the flaming fires were extinguished in their places.\nوَبِسُلْطَانِکَ الَّذِیْ عُرِفَتْ لَکَ بِہِ الْغَلَبَۃُ دَہْرَ الدُّہُوْرِ \nWA BE SULTAANEKAL LAZE O’REFAT LAKA BEHIL GHALABATO DAHRAD DOHOORE \nAnd I beseech You through Your might, through which You have been known to be All-powerful for ever and ever,\nوَ حُمِدْتَ بِہٖ فِی السَّمٰوٰتِ وَ الْاَرْضِیْنَ \nWA HOMID-TA BEHI FIS SAMAAWAATE WAL ARAZEENA, \nand for which You have been praised in the heavens and the earth;\nوَ بِکَلِمَتِکَ کَلِمَۃِ الصِّدْقِ الَّتِیْ سَبَقَتْ لِاَبِیْنَا آدَمَ عَلَیْہِ السَّلَامُ وَ ذُرِّیَّتِہٖ بِالرَّحْمَۃِ \nWA BEKALEMATEKA KALEMATIS SIDQIL LATEE SABAQAT LE-ABEENAA AADAMA A’LAYHIS SALAAMO WA ZURRIYYATEHI BIR-RAHMATE \nand I beseech You through Your word, the Word of Truth, which became a blessing for our father Adam and his generation;\nوَ اَسْئَلُکَ بِکَلِمَتِکَ الَّتِیْ غَلَبَتْ کُلَّ شَیْءٍ \nWA AS-ALOKA BE KALEMATEKAL LATEE GHALABAT KULLA SHAY-IN, \nand I beseech You through Your word, by which You overcame everything;\nوَّ بِنُوْرِ وَجْہِکَ الَّذِیْ تَجَلَّیْتَ بِہٖ لِلْجَبَلِ \nWA BE NOORE WAJHEKAL LAZEE TAJALLAYTA BEHI LIL JABALE \nand I beseech You through the light of Your Face, which when it flased on Mount Sinai\nفَجَعَلْتَہٗ دَکًّا \nFA-JA-A’LTAHU DAKKAA \ncrushed it to pieces,\nوَّ خَرَّ مُوْسٰی صَعِقًا \nWA KHARRA MOOSAA SA-E’QAA, \nwhereby Moosa fainted and fell down,\nوَ بِمَجْدِکَ الَّذِیْ ظَہَرَ عَلٰی طُوْرِ سَیْنَآءَ \nWA BE MAJDEKAL LAZEE ZAHARA A’LAA TORE SAYNAAA-A \nand through Your Glory, which appeared on Mount Sinai,\nفَکَلَّمْتَ بِہٖ عَبْدَکَ وَ رَسُوْلَکَ مُوْسَی ابْنَ عِمْرَانَ \nFA-KALLAMTA BEHI A’BDAKA WA RASOOLAKA MOOSABNE I’MRAANA, \nand through which You addressed Your slave and Your Mesenger; Moosa, son of Imran,\nوَ بِطَلْعَتِکَ فِیْ سَاعِیْرَ \nWA BE TAL-A’TEKA FEE SAA-E’ERA \nand through Your appearance in Sa'ir\nوَ ظُہُوْرِکَ فِیْ جَبَلِ فَارَانَ \nWA ZOHOOREKA FEE JABALE FAARAANA \nand on Mount Faran\nبِرَبَوَاتِ الْمُقَدَّسِیْنَ \nBE-RABAWAATIL MOQADDASEENA \nnear Rabawat, which are clean and holy places,\nوَ جُنُوْدِ الْمَلآئِکَۃِ الصَّافِّیْنَ \nWA JONOODIL MALAAA-EKATIS SAAF-FEENA \nwhen troops of heavenly angels were in rows,\nوَ خُشُوْعِ الْمَلآئِکَۃِ الْمُسَبِّحِیْنَ \nWA KHOSHOO-E’L MALAAA-EKATIL MOSABBEHEENA, \nand with the submissiveness of the angels praising You,\nبِبَرَکَاتِکَ الَّتِیْ بَارَکْتَ فِیْہَا عَلٰی اِبْرَاہِیْمَ خَلِیْلِکَ عَلَیْہِ السَّلَامُ \nWA BE-BARAKAATEKAL LATEE BAARAKTA FEEHAA A’LAA IBRAAHEEMA KHALEELEKA A’LAYHIS SALAAMO \nand with Your blessings with which You honoured Abraham, Your sincere friend, peace be upon him,\nفِیْ اُمَّۃِ مُحَمَّدٍ صَلَّی اللہُ عَلَیْہِ وَ اٰلِہٖ \nFEE UMMATE MOHAMMADIN SALLAL LAAHO A'LAYHE WA AALEHI\namong the followers of Muhammad, Your blessings be upon him and his Progeny\nوَ بَارَکْتَ لِاِسْحَاقَ صَفِیِّکَ \nWA BAARAKTA LE-ISHAAQA SAFIYYEKA \nand You honoured Ishaaq, Your chosen prophet,\nفِیْ اُمَّۃِ عِیْسٰی عَلَیْہِمَا السَّلَامُ \nFEE UMMATE E’ESAA A’LAYHEMAS SALAAMO, \namong the followers of Eesaa, peace be on them both,\nوَ بَارَکْتَ لِیَعْقُوْبَ اِسْرٰئِیْلِکَ \nWA BAARAKTA LE YA’QOOBA ISRAAA-EELEKA \nand honoured Yaqoob, Your favoured slave,\nفِیْ اُمَّۃِ مُوْسَی عَلَیْہِمَا السَّلَامُ \nFEE UMMATE MOOSAA A’LAYHEMAS SALAAMO, \namong the followers of Moses, peace be on them both,\nوَ بَارَکْتَ لِحَبِیْبِکَ مُحَمَّدٍ صَلَّي اللہُ عَلَیْہِ وَ اٰلِہٖ \nWA BAARAKTA LE HABIBEKA MOHAMMADIN SALLALLAAHO A’LAYHE WA AALEHI \nand honoured Your intimate friend Muhammad, may the blessings of Allah be upon him and his Progeny,\nفِیْ عِتْرَتِہٖ وَ ذُرِّیَّتِہٖ وَ اُمَّتِہٖ \nFEE I’TRATEHI WA ZURRIYYATEHI WA UMMATEHI, \namong his offspring and progeny, and his followers\nاَللّٰہُمَّ وَ کَمَا غِبْنَا عَنْ ذٰلِکَ وَ لَمْ نَشْہَدْہُ \nALLAAHUMMA WA KAMAA GHIBNAA A’N ZAALEKA WA LAM NASH-HAD-HO \nO Allah! Just as were absent and didn’t witness these manifestations of Your glory,\nوَ اٰمَنَّا بِہٖ وَ لَمْ نَرَہٗ صِدْقًا وَّ عَدْلًا \nWA AAMANNAA BEHI WA LAM NARAHU SIDQAN WA A’DLAA \nyet we believed in their truth and justice, without having been eyewitnesses,\nاَنْ تُصَلِّیَ عَلٰی مُحَمَّدٍ وَّ اٰلِ مُحَمَّدٍ \nAN TOSALLEYA A’LAA MOHAMMADIN WA AALE MOHAMMADIN \nSo we beseech You to send Your blessings upon Muhammad and the Progeny of Muhammad,\nوَّ اَنْ تُبَارِکَ عَلٰی مُحَمَّدٍ وَّ اٰلِ مُحَمَّدٍ \nWA A’N TOBAAREKA A’LAA MOHAMMADIN WA AALE MOHAMMADIN \nand honour Muhammad and the Progeny of Muhamamad,\nوَّ تَرَحَّمَ عَلٰی مُحَمَّدٍ وَّاٰلِ مُحَمَّدٍ \nWA TARAHHAMA A’LAA MOHAMMADIN WA AALE MOHAMMADIN \nand have mercy on Muhammad and the Progeny of Muhammad,\nکَاَفْضَلِ مَا صَلَّیْتَ وَ بَارَکْتَ وَ تَرَحَّمْتَ \nKA-AFZALE MAA SALLAYTA WA BAARAKTA WA TARAHHAMTA\nwith the blessings, honour, and mercy\nعَلٰی اِبْرَاحِیْمَ وَ اٰلِ اِبْرَاہِیْمَ \nA’LAA IBRAAHEEMA WA AALE IBRAAHEEMA \nyou sent and bestowed on Abraham and the progeny of Abraham.\nاِنَّکَ حَمِیْدٌ مُّجِیْدٌ \nINNAKA HAMEEDUM MAJEEDUN \nSurely You are Praiseworthy, Glorious,\nفَعَّالٌ لِّمَا تُرِیْدُ \nFA-A’ALUL LEMAA TOREEDO \nthe Doer of what You will.\nوَ اَنْتَ عَلٰی کُلِّ شَیْءٍ قَدِیْرٌ.\nWA ANTA A’LAA KULLE SHAY-IN QADEERUN.\nYou are Powerful over all things\n\nNow one should express his legitimate desire and beseech Allah to fulfill it, then recite the following:\nیَا حَنَّانُ یَا مَنَّانُ \nYAA HANNAANO YAA MANNAANO \nO Compassionate, O Kind\nیَا بَدِیْعَ السَّمٰوٰتِ وَ الْاَرْضِ \nYAA BADEE-A’S SAMAAWAATE WAL ARZE \nO Original Designer of Heavens and Earth\nیَا ذَا الْجَلَالِ وَ الْاِکْرَامِ یَا اَرْحَمَ الرَّاحِمِیْنَ \nYAA ZAL-JALAALE WAL IKRAAME YAA ARHAMAR RAAHEMEENA \nO Lord of Glory and Honour O most Merciful of all the merciful.\nاَللّٰہُمَّ بِحَقِّ ہٰذَا الدُّعَآءِ \nALLAAHUMMA BEHAQQE HAAZAD DO-A’AA-E \nO Allah, for the sake of this prayer, \nوَ بِحَقِّ ہٰذِہِ الْاَسْمَآءِ \nWA BE HAQQE HAAZEHIL ASMAAA-IL \nand for the sake of these Names \nالَّتِیْ لَا یَعْلَمُ تَفْسِیْرَہَا وَ لَا یَعْلَمُ بَاطِنَہَا غَیْرُکَ \nLATEE LAA YA’LAMO TAFSEERAHAA WA LAA TAAWEELOHAA WA LAA BAATENAHAA WA LAA ZAAHERAHAA GHAIROKA \nwhich no one can interpret, the inner meaning of which no one other than Yourself knows.\nصَلِّ عَلٰی مُحَمَّدٍ وَّ اٰلِ مُحَمَّدٍ \nSALLE A’LAA MOHAMMADIN WA AALE MOHAMMADIN \nSend Your blessing upon Muhammad and the Progeny of Muhammad; \nوَّ افْعَلْ بِیْ مَا اَنْتَ اَہْلُہٗ وَ لَا تَفْعَلْ بِیْ مَا اَنَا اَہْلُہٗ \nWAF-A’L BEE MAA ANTA AHLOHU WA LAA TAF-A’L BEE MAA ANAA AHLOHU \nand do to me what suits You and do not do to me what I deserve\nوَ اغْفِرْ لِیْ مِنْ ذُنُوْبِیْ مَا تَقَدَّمَ مِنْہَا وَ مَا تَاَخَّرَ \nWAGHFIRLEE MIN ZONOOBI MAA TAQADDAMA MINHAA WA MAA TA-AKH-KHARA \nand forgive my sins past and future, \nوَ وَسِّعْ عَلَیَّ مِنْ حَلَالِ رِزْقِکَ \nWA WASSE’ A’LAYYAA MIN HALAALE RIZQEKA \nand increase Your lawful sustenance for me,\nوَ اکْفِنِیْ مَؤُنَۃَ اِنْسَانِ سَوْءٍ وَّ جَارِ سَوْءٍ \nWAK-FENEE MAOONATA INSAANE SAW-IN WA JAARE SAW-INW \nand save me from the help of wicked men, wicked neighbours, \nوَّ قَرِیْنِ سَوْءٍ وَّ سُلْطَانِ سَوْءٍ \nWA QAREENE SAW-INW WA SULTAANE SAW-INW \nwicked companions, and wicked rulers\nاِنَّکَ عَلٰی مَا تَشَآءُ قَدِیْرٌ \nINNAKA A'LAA MAA TASHAA-O QADEERUN.\nVerily You are able to do whatever You will, \nوَ بِکُلِّ شَیْءٍ عَلِیْمٌ \nWA BE-KULLE SHAY-IN A'LEEM.\nand You know everything. \nاٰمِیْنَ رَبَّ الْعَالَمِیْنَ.\nAAMEEN RABBAL A'ALAMEEN.\nAameen, O Lord of the worlds.\n\nAl-Majlisi (r.a.) narrated from Sayed Ibn Baqi’s ‘Al-Misbah’ that one should say after reciting Dua al-Simaat:\nاَللّٰہُمَّ بِحَقِّ ہٰذَا الدُّعَآءِ \nALLAAHUMMA BEHAQQE HAAZAD DO-A’AA-E \nO Allah For the sake of this prayer,\nوَ بِحَقِّ ہٰذِہِ الْاَسْمَآءِ \nWA BE HAQQE HAAZEHIL ASMAAA-IL \nand for the sake of these Names\nالَّتِیْ لَا یَعْلَمُ تَفْسِیْرَہَا وَ لَا تَاْوِیْلَہَا \nLATEE LAA YA’LAMO TAFSEERAHAA WA LAA TAAWEELOHAA \nwhich no one can interpret,\nوَلَا بَاطِنَہَا وَ لَا ظَاہِرَہَا غَیْرُکَ \nWA LAA BAATENAHAA WA LAA ZAAHERAHAA GHAIROKA \nthe inner and outer meaning of which no one other than Your self knows.\nاَنْ تُصَلِّیَ عَلٰی مُحَمَّدٍ وَّ اٰلِ مُحَمَّدٍ \nAN TOSALLE A’LAA MOHAMMADIN WA AALE MOHAMMADIN \nSend Your blessing upon Muhammad and the Progeny of Muhammad;\nوَ اَنْ تَرْزُقَنِیْ خَیْرَ الدُّنْیَا وَ الْاٰخِرَۃِ.\nWA AN TARZOQANEE KHARAD DUNYAA WAL AAKHERAH\nand give me the good of this world and the hereafter;\nوَ افْعَلْ بِیْ مَا اَنْتَ اَہْلُہٗ \nWAF-A’L BEE MAA ANTA AHLOHU \nand do to me what suits You\nوَ لَا تَفْعَلْ بِیْ مَا اَنَا اَہْلُہٗ \nWA LAA TAF-A’L BEE MAA ANAA AHLOHU \nand do not do to me what I deserve\nوَ انْتَقِمْ لِیْ مِنْ...\nWANTAQIM LEE MIN…\nName your enemy than say:\nوَ اغْفِرْ لِیْ مِنْ ذُنُوْبِیْ \nWAGHFIRLEE MIN ZONOOBI \nand forgive my sins\nمَا تَقَدَّمَ مِنْہَا وَ مَا تَاَخَّرَ \nMAA TAQADDAMA MINHAA WA MAA TA-AKH-KHARA \npast and future,\nوَ لِوَالِدَیَّ وَ لِجَمِیْعِ الْمُؤْمِنِیْنَ وَ اْلمُؤْمِنَاتِ \nWA LE WAALEDAYYAA WA LE JAMEE-I’L MO-MENEENA WAL MOMENAATE \nand forgive my parents and all faithful men and women,\nوَ وَسِّعْ عَلَیَّ مِنْ حَلَالِ رِزْقِکَ \nWA WASSE’ A’LAYYAA MIN HALAALE RIZQEKA \nand increase Your lawful sustenance for me,\nوَ اکْفِنِیْ مَؤُنَۃَ اِنْسَانِ سَوْءٍ \nWAK-FENEE MAOONATA INSAANE SAW-IN \nand save me from the help of wicked men,\nوَّ جَارِ سَوْءٍ وَّ سُلْطَانِ سَوْءٍ \nWA JAARE SAW-INW WA SULTAANE SAW-INW \nwicked neighbours, wicked rulers,\nوَّ قَرِیْنِ سَوْءٍ وَّ یَوْمِ سَوْءٍ وَّ سَاعَۃِ سَوْءٍ \nWA QAREENE SAW-INW WA YAWME SAW-INW WA SAA-A’TE SAW-IN \nwicked companions, and evil days, and evil hours,\nوَ انْتَقِمْ لِیْ مِمَّنْ یَکِیْدُنِیْ \nWANTAQIM LEE MIMMAN YAKEEDONEE \nand exact vengeance for me on everyone who hatches secret plots against me,\nوَ مِمَّنْ یَبْغِیْ عَلَیَّ وَ یُرِیْدُ بِیْ وَ بِاَہْلِیْ \nWA MIMMAN YABGHEE A’LAYYA WA YOREEDO BEE WA BE AHLEE \nand on everyone who oppresses me and seeks to do to me or my family\nوَ اَوْلَادِیْ وَ اِخْوَانِیْ \nWA AWLAADEE WA IKHWAANEE \nor my children or my brothers\nوَ جِیْرَانِیْ وَ قَرَابَاتِیْ مِنَ الْمُؤْمِنِیْنَ وَ الْمُؤْمِنَاتِ ظُلْمًا\nWA JEERAANI WA QARAABATI MENAL MOMENEENA WAL MOMENAATE ZULMAN \nor my neighbours or my relations among faithful men and women. (seeks to do) injustice\nاِنَّکَ عَلٰی مَا تَشَآءُ قَدِیْرٌ \nINNAKA A’LAA MAA TASHAAA-O QADEERUN \nVerily You are able to do whatever You will,\nوَّ بِکُلِّ شَیْءٍ عَلِیْمٌ \nWA BE KULLE SHAY’IN A’LEEMUN \nand You know everything.\nاٰمِیْنَ رَبَّ الْعٰلَمِیْنَ. \nAAMEEN RABBAL A’AALAMEEN\nAameen, O Lord of the worlds.\n\nThen say:\nاَللّٰہُمَّ بِحَقِّ ہٰذَا الدُّعَآءِ \nALLAAHUMMA BEHAQQE HAAZAD DO-A’AA-E \nO Allah! For the sake of this prayer,\nتَفَضَّلْ عَلٰی فُقَرَآءِ الْمُؤْمِنِیْنَ وَ الْمُؤْمِنَاتِ بِالْغِنٰی وَ الثَّرْوَۃِ \nTAFAZZAL A’LAA FOQARAAA-IL MOMENEENA WAL MOMENAATE BIL GHENAA WAS SARWATE \ngrant wealth and affluence to indigent faithful men and women,\nوَ عَلٰی مَرْضَی الْمُؤْمِنیْنَ وَ الْمُؤْمِنَاتِ بِالشِّفَآءِ وَ الصِّحَّۃِ\nWA A’LAA MARZAL MOMENEENA WAL MOMENAATE BISH-SHEFAA-E WAS-SEHATE \nand recovery and sound health to the sick faithful men and women,\nوَ عَلٰی اَحْیَآءِ الْمُؤْمِنِیْنَ وَ الْمُؤْمِنَاتِ بِاللُّطْفِ وَ الْکَرَامَۃِ\nWA A’LAA AHYAAA-IL MOMENEENA WAL MOMENAATE BIL-LUTFE WAL KARAAMATE \nand bliss and clemency to the living faithful men and women,\nوَ عَلٰی اَمْوَاتِ الْمُؤْمِنِیْنَ وَ الْمُؤْمِنَاتِ بِالْمَغْفِرَۃِ وَ الرَّحْمَۃِ\nWA A’LAA AMWAATIL MOMENEENA WAL MOMENAATE BIL MAGHFERATE WAR-RAHMATE \nand remit the sins of, and have mercy on, the deceased faithful men and women,\nوَ عَلٰی مُسَافِرِی الْمُؤْمِنِیْنَ وَ الْمْؤْمِنَاتِ بِالرَّدِّ اِلٰی اَوْطَانِہِمْ سَالِمِیْنَ غَانِمِیْنَ \nWA A’LAA MOSAAFERIL MOMENEENA WAL MOMENAATE BIR-RADDE ELAA AWTAANEHIM SAALEMEENA GHAANEMEENA \nand arrange the return home of all faithful travellers with safety and gain.\nبِرَحْمَتِکَ یَا اَرْحَمَ الرَّاحِمِیْنَ \nBE RAHMATEKA YAA ARHAMAR RAAHEMEENA \nThrough Your mercy, O Most Merciful of all the merciful.\nوَ صَلَّی اللهُ عَلٰی سَیِّدِنَا مُحَمَّدٍ خَاتَمِ النَّبِیِّیْنَ \nWA SALLALLAAHO A’LAA SAYYEDENAA MOHAMMADIN KHAATAMIN NABIYYEENA \nMay Allah’s blessings be upon our master Muhammad, the seal of the prophets,\nوَ عِتْرَتِہِ الطَّاہِرِیْنَ \nWA I’TRATEHIT TAAHERAANA \nand his Progeny, the purified.\nوَ سَلَّمَ تَسْلِیْمًا کَثِیْرًا.\nWA SALLAMA TASLEEMAN KASEERAN\nand His peace be upon them plentifully\n\nSheikh Ibn Fahad narrates that it is recommended after reciting Dua al-Semaat to recite the following:\n اَللّٰہُمَّ اِنِّیْ اَسْئَلُکَ بِحُرْمَۃِ ہٰذَا الدُّعَآءِ \nALLAAHUMMA INNEE AS-ALOKA BE HURMATE HAAZEID-DO-A’AAA-E \nO Allah I ask you for the sake of this prayer\nوَ بِمَا فَاتَ مِنْہُ مِنَ الْاَسْمَآءِ \nWA BEMAA FAATA MINHO MENAL AS-MAAA-E \nand what was mentioned in it from names\nوَ بِمَا یَشْتَمِلُ عَلَیْہِ مِنَ التَّفْسِیْرِ وَ التَّدْبِیْرِ \nWA BEMAA YASHTAMELO A’LAYHE MENAT-TAFSEERE WAT-TADBEERIL \nand what it contains from meanings and design\nالَّذِیْ لَا یُحِیْطُ بِہٖ اِلَّا اَنْتَ \nLAZEE LAA YOHEETO BEHI ILLAA ANTA \nwhich none other than You comprehend fully\nاَنْ تَفْعَلَ بِیْ...\nAN TAF-A’LA BEE...\nthat you do to me …\nmention your legitimate needs.", 
    "title": "Dua Simat"
}